  "prompt": "How can I know who views my Instagram profile?",
  "response": "Unfortunately, Instagram does not provide a direct feature to see who views your profile. While there are third-party apps and websites claiming to offer this service, they are typically not reliable and may pose security risks. Instagram only provides:\n\n1. Insights for business and creator accounts, which show:\n- Profile visits\n- Reach\n- Impressions\n- Follower demographics\n\n2. Story Views, which show who has viewed your Instagram Stories within 24 hours.\n\nFor personal accounts, there's no official way to know exactly who has viewed your profile. Be cautious of any apps or websites claiming otherwise, as they might be scams or compromise your account security.",
